# See also

This docs site is the *published* surface. The operational source of truth lives in the repo root —
open these files in the repository:

- **`README.md`** — project overview and quickstart.
- **`SECRETS.md`** — secrets and environment parity.
- **`DEPLOY.md`** — deployment.
- **`SERVICES.md`** — the service topology.

> These live alongside this docs site in the repo root (outside `documentation/`), so they are not
> rendered into the site; they stay the canonical operational reference and link back up to here.

For cross-cutting framework conventions (quality gates, the review system, batteries, upgrading), see the
framework's published docs: <https://cdowell-swtr.github.io/swiftwater-framework/>.
